{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_data_ver01/data/sn87055779/00517016998/1924041201/0149.xml":{"full_text":"15 CONFIRMATIONS\nSUNDAY, ST. PETER\u2019S\nNumber Included Eight\nAdults\u2014Other Church\nNotes.\nAt the regular St. Peter's Evan\ngelical Luthem church service Sun\nday at 10 o\u2019clock seven catechumen*\nwill renew their baptismal vow and\ntoe received Into full communion with\nthe church by the sacred rite of con\nfirmation. The members of the class\nere: lister Kraus, Arnold Voel\nkort, Beulah Roeder, Lucile Myers,\nJ.uella Benzel, Deona Forstbauer and\nCharlotte Myers- The service will\nbe In the English language.\nThe pastor. Rev. Otto Turk, will\ndeliver an address on, \u201cFaithful\nConfessors of Christ.\u2019\u2019 Miss Clara\nFlschmann will sing a solo, the Sun\nday school will sing. \u201cFaithful Unto\nDeath Abide,\u201d and the confirmation\nclass, \u201cSpeak Now, Dord, Thy Amen.\u201d\nImmediately after this service a pri\nvate service will be held In whcih\neight adult members will be received\nInto membership with the church by\nbaptism and confirmation.\nTho Hunnday school will be held,\nns usual, at 9 a. m., tyid the Bible\nhour at 6:30 p. m. On Good Friday\ncommunion services will be held in\nthe German language at 7:30 p. m.\nAnnouncements requested on Wed\nnesday. Social gathering of Junior\nWalther Eeaguo Wednesday, at 7:30\np. in-, at parish hall.\nFirst Baptist Church.\nBible school at 9:45 a. m. In\ncharge of F. W. Porter. Morning\nworship at 10:45 a. m. Evangelist A.\nH. Bond will speak. Voluntary, \u201cI\nDove to Tell the 'Story,\u201d toy Ashford;\noffertory, \u201cTo a Wood Violet,\u201d by\nW. M- Fulton. B. Y. P. U. at 6:30;\ndeacon's prayer meeting at 6:50;\nsong service at 7:30;\u201dTlvangelist Bond\nwill give the first exposition of the\nBook of Daniel. The Bible confer\nence will continue every afternoon\nand evening until Saturday. Special\ndelegations will attend throughout\nthe week. Monday evening the Bap\ntist Boosters, Tuesday evening, the\nEoyal Women, Samuel and the Help\ning Hand Bible classes will attend;\nWednesday evening the Boy Scouts,\nthe C. I. C. and the Maranatha Bible\nclass; Thursday* evening, the Delta\nAlpha and the Modern Mohican Bi\nble classes will attend;.Friday eve\nning, there will be a banquet for the\nMoody Bible Institute alumni of\nNorthern Indiana at 6:SO. The vol\nI\nPhone\nMishawaka\n10\nMishawaka Classified\nANNOUNCEMENTS\nPersonals.\nCARP OP THANKS Vanacher. He\nwish to express our heartfelt appreci\nation to the friends for the sympathy\nand kindness shown us during the\nIllness and death of our husband and\nfather. Also for the beautiful floral\ntributes. Signed,\nMRS. HENRY VANACHER\nAND CHILDREN. _\nlost and Found._10\nLOST\u2014Bunch of keys. Return to News\nTimes office, Mishawaka, 120 Lincoln\nW. W. Reward.\nautomobiles\nAutomobile Tire*. 1M\nTilt Eft New and used. Low price*\nTires guaranteed. Llnaeamler_Tlra\nShop. 222S Lincoln Way West. Misha\nV s k R _\nBUSINESS SERVICE\nBusiness Service Offered. 18\nGOUT/. ANI) SONS\u2014Sanitary plumbing\nand hooting; repair work a specialty.\nEstimates cheerfully given. 2501 W. 6th\nat. Rhone Mlsli. 2<BU._\nPainting\u2014Papering.\n84\nCARTERS DUTCH BOY Lead, 100 tba.\n*13.50; 6C0 Itm. *13. C. F. Cook, CM.\nanaker and Fourth Sta. Mlah. 1608.\nProfessional Services. 27\nSFE ROBERT E. LEE for advanced\nchiropractic service. Formerly of Lee\nA- loeffler. South Bend. Now located\nnt 510 N. Main St., Mishawaka. I\u2019hone\nMlsli. 2i',IS. 9-tf\nWanted\u2014Business Service. SI\nUPHOLSTERING and repairing. Mish\nawaka l'ph\".V<tering Co., 117 W. Front.\nPhone Mish. SOS. l--t2\nEMPLOYMENT\nHelp Wanted\u2014Male. S3\nWANTED\u2014Good house man; ciperlenc\ned, good (references. Schuyler Rose,\n402 Lincoln Way B. _\nSALESMEN. ATTENTION\u2014Au oppojtu\nnity for Uve-wlro hustlers; men wil\nling to work. W\u00bb will put you In the\nbig money class. Wo are offering the\nbest closo-ln sub-division In the city;\nbi