t H. Miller, pastor.\nSunday school at 9:30 a. m. Morning\nworship at 10:45. Study hour ar.d\nrehearsal of Easter music at 7:30\np. m. Wednesday and Friday.\nRev. Alonzo B. Garman, mission\nary superintendent of Michigan\nSynod of the United Lutheran church\nwill he In the city Saturday. He\nwill meet with the church council\nat 6:30 p. m. Saturday to consider\nthe renewal of the pastor\u2019s com\nmission for another year as home\nmissionary.\nFree Methodist\nCorner Chestnut arid Grove sts.,\nSunday school, 9.30 a. m. Mr.\nOrpha McDuffie, superintendent.\nPreaching at 10:45 a. m. and 7:30\np. m. Cottage prayer meetings\nThursday evening. Noon hour gos\npel services at Dodge\u2019s Tuesday and\nFriday. Rev. R. G. Wilkins, pas\ntor.\nSt. Paul\u2019s Episcopal\nL. C. Rogers, rector. Palm Sun\nday services; Holy Eucharist at\n7:30 a. m. Church school at 9:45.\nProcession of the palms service and\nsermon at 11 a. m. Evening ser\nvice and sermon at 7:30 o'clock.\nCoalbusb Evangelical\nRev. Earl F. Snyder, pastor. 9:30\na. m. Sunday school. Andrew God\nehall, Supt. 10:30 a. m. sermon\u2014\nREAL ESTATE FOR SALE\nHouses For Sale.\n84\nKOR SAMS\u20143 room cottage, lathe and\nplastered, tj acre of ground, $1,500,\neasy terras. Seymour Jansen. Fhone\nMishawaka 1272.lltf. _\nFOR SALE\u2014Six room bungalow, strict\"\nly modern, good location. Hot water\nheat, immediate possession. Call Mish.\n1363._ Bt7\nSPECIAL bargains, two 4-room bouses,'\nall finished and ready to more in;\nmust be sold at once, so don't delay;\nterms, $50 cash. Prices $1,900 and $2,000.\nM. L. Petro. Phans Mish. 183. 21 tf\n$200 DOWN\u2014New four-room house; good\nlocation, 14th St. Pay for it like rent.\nColpaert Realty Corp. Phone Mish.\nimi. 6-tf\nVoR SALE\u201410-room house;' vacant; all\nmodern; close in. $1,000 down, bal\nance like rent. Ostrander, Photog\nrapher.12-tl\nNEW, MODERN 5-room bungalow.\nState and Homewood. Terms. Wil\nliam Meinke, 124 Indiana At. 12-t2\nFOR SALE.\nThree acres near Station 7, close to\nLincoln Way East, with 5-room bun\ngalow and garage. Some small fruit.\nPrice $3,000. About $1,800 cash re\nquired.\nNew five-room bungalow, all mod\nern. Just completed. Corner lot on\nState St. $5,000.\nNew five-room bungalow, one block\nfrom Lincoln Highway and car line,\njust completed and ready for occu\npancy. SoiUd hardwood floors in two\nrooms, gum trim and colonades, laun\ndry tubs in basement. Fine large cor\nner lot. $6,000.\nSix-room, 2-story house, all modern,\nwith garage, on East Third St. Pav\ning paid. $5,000.\nFine large lot on Lincoln Way East,\nacross the street from the new. High\nSchool. $2,000.\nAnother lot just beyond Byrkit Av\nenue, on Llncola Way East, at $1,300.\nIf vou wish to buy a vacant lot in\nany part of the city, it will pay you\nto see us before buying elsewhere.\nSTARK REALTY CO., Realtors.\n120 Lincoln Way East. 6-t7\nFOR SALE\u20148 room all modern home,\ndonble garage, vapor heating system,\nlargo lot. Ideal residential district.\nX'rice and terms RIGHT.\nFive room bungalow, $2,700, terms.\nNew 8 room house, River Park, terms.\nFour room house, $1,150, terms, bal\nance $12.50 per month. All modern 4\nroom bungalow, terms. New 5 room\nbungalow, $3,400, terms. Six room\nhouse, $3,000, terms. New colonial\nhome, priced for a sure sale. Five\nroom bungalow, $3,<00, terms. Eight\nroom house, large lot on paved street,\n$4,000, terms.\nSeven room house, E. Third st., close\nto car line, large lot with fruit trees,\n$4,000, terms. Five room house, gar\nage, lot 66 ft. square, $2,650, terms.\nNew 4 room house, garage, furnace,\nfull acre of ground, cash or E-Z terms.\nNew 4 room houses, acres or half\nacres, electric lights, located in Maple\nHurst Place, call\nGEO. F. EBERHART SONS\nFarmers Bank Bldg. 8ulte A. B.\nPhone Mish. 270 or Gar. 21-F-2.\nBOFSES located in all parts of the city.\nBee Geo. Walton, over Wtney\u2019a Store.\nPhone Mish. 590\u20141593. _ 9-tf\nNEW BFNGALOW\n$300 DOWN\nNew and strictly modern bungalow.\nContaining five rooms and completely\nequipped bath. Basement under entire\nhouse. Floor drain. Connections for\nlaundry tuba. Combination water heat\ner. i>1nk and buttt in cupboard in kitch\nen. Double floors over entire house.\nSolid oak floors In living room and\ndining room. Book case colonades. In\nterior neatly finished in light oak. Two\nnice bed rooms with spacious closet\nin each. Linen closet In hallway. Bath\nfinished in white enamel. Porch Heroes\nfront. Good sixed lot. Close In on South\nside.\nCOLPAERT REALTY CORPORATION\n136-8 Lincoln way Weet.\nPhone Mish. 1181.\nltt-t-f.\nNEW 5-ROOM, all modern, all ivory and\nwhite enamel: walls decorated; $3,700.\n1532 E. Fourth. Another 5-room, $3,000.\n_ 8-tf\nSmall Houses\nWe atill have a few email houses to\n\u2022ell for $50 down, and small weekly\npayments. Ready to move into. Quick\naction on your part wll secure on* of\nthese.\nSecurities Investment Corporation.\n216 S. Lafayette Bird. Phone Lin. 6007 j\nOpen Evenings.\nsubject: \u201cThe Saddest Story Ever\nTold.\" 7:00 p. m. E. L. C. E. meet\ning.\nLOCAL CLUB WOMEN TO\nBANQUET YOUNG PEOPLE\nOF COUNTY CHURCHES\nYoun g people of aU county\nchurches will be entertained by the\nEast Mishawaka Mothers\u2019 club at a\nsupper to be served at the First M.\nE. church April 29, according to\na decision reached at a meeting of\nthe club held Thunsday afternoon\nof Mrs. Nelson O. Culp, 948 Wash\nington av.\nThe club also named the follow\ning committee to be in charge of\nthe fancy work booth at a bazaar\nto be held in November: Mrs. Wal\nlace Laps, Mrs. W. E. Weldy. Mre.\nWalter Niles.\nRev. Royer, of Osceola, delivered\na short talk at Thursday\u2019s club\nmeeting, using as his theme, \u201cThe\u2022\nPerfect Woman.\u201d Refreshments\nwere served by Mrs. Culp and com\nmittee.\nYou will like the \u2019President*\n\u2014-advt. ll-t-2\nSUNDAY SCHOOL CLASS\nELECTS NEW OFFICERS\nMise Donabelle Walker was elect\ned president of the Swastika class of\nthe Immanuel Baptist Sunday school\nat their regular meeting Thursday\nevening at the home of Mias Donna\nbelle Moore, W. Marion st., Miss Inez\nReed, vice president; Mias Martha\nMcCay, secretary; Athalyn Roberts,\ntreasurer and Mias Helen Glass,\nchairman of the social committee.\nDuring the business session plans\nwere completed for a \u201cweiner\u201d roast\nwhich will be held Thursday, April\n17. A social evening followed the\nbusiness transacted. Refreshments\nwere served. The next meeting will\nbe at the home of Miss Helen Glass,\nSouth Bend.\n'President* is non-partisan.\n\u2014advt. ll-t-2\nSUNSHINE CLUB MEETS.\nThe Sunshine club held its regu\nlar meeting Thursday afternoon at\nthe home of Mrs. Florence Kracke,\n1015 Quinley st.. South Bend. A\npiano duet by Mrs. Mary Haynes\nand Mrs. Grace Ravencroft and a\npiano solo by Mrs. Ida Johnson\ncomprised the entertainment pro\ngram. The next meeting will be\nheld at the Home of Mrs. Laura\nCobb, 613 N. 23rd st.\nVISITING PARENTS\nMrs. John Baranoski, and two\nchildren, 521 W. Lawrence st., left\nThursday for Meriden, Conn., where\nshe will visit with her parents and\nrelatives.\nYou will vote for \u201cPresident.\u2019\n\u2014advt. ll-t-2\nGOING TO BUILD?\nIf you want your work done right\nand at the right price, see\nDALTON MANN\nCONTRACTORS BUILDERS\nPhone 133, Osceola\nHOUSES\nFor Sale\nMISHAWAKA\n1\u20145 room W. 7th St.$46W\n1\u20145 room East 11th St. ..>.$5000\n1\u20147 room West Fourth StC..$4500\n1\u20145 room East Fourth Stt. ..$5000\n1\u20146 room Lincoln way E $8250\n1\u20145 room, S. Hendricks.$3400\nLOTS IN EAST END $50 DOWN\nSOUTH BEND\n1\u20146 room Woodward Av.$9500\n1\u201412 room East Monroe ..$17,000\n1\u20145 room South High .$6350\n1\u20145 room N. College St.$4950\n1\u20146 room S. Robinson.$4,750\n8\u20143 room So. East.$50 Down\nLOTS IN NO. WEST $60 DOWN\n1\u201445 acre farm Dixie Highway\nat .$5500\nIf you have a liouse for Bale phone\nFisher. He can sell It.\nS. D. FISHER\nPhone Mlsb. 779\nC. OF C. LUNGHERS\nTO HEAR ADDRESS\nON BUSINESS CYCLE\nSales Manager of .Beckwith\nCorp., to Speak at Tues\nday Session.\nJames F. Potts, sales manager of\nthe Beckwith corp., Dowagiae,\nMich., will deliver an address on\n\u201cThe Business Outlook\u201d at the nejft\nmonthly meeting of the Mishawaka\nChamber of Commerce to be held\nTuesday noon at Hotel Mishawaka.\nThe Beckwith corp., is one of the\nlargest manufacturing concerns in\nthe country and because of the\nclose study Mr. Potts has given eco\nnomic conditions ltis expected his\naddress will provide a fund of In\nformation of the future business\noutlook for the country.\nChamber of Commerce officials\nrequested Friday that reservations\nfor the luncheon next Tuesday be\nmade as nearly as possible.\nWANTS SITE OFFER.\nA request was issued Friday by\nMrs. Schuyler Rose, chairman of\nthe Y. W. C. A. headquarters\u2019 com\nmittee, that all persons in the city\nowning property available for site\nfor the proposed association, building\ncommunicate with the committee\nas soon as possible.\nTO VISIT IN TEXAS\nDr. I* M. Walton, Lincoln way E.,\nleft Wednesday for a three weeks\u2019\nvisit with friends in Corsicana,\nTexas.\nWtlcoine the \u2018President;.\u2019\n\u2014advt. H-t-2\nNow Showing!\n\u201cKENTUCKY\nDAYS\u201d\nA story of the\nearly pioneers!\nAlso\n\u201cThe Way Of\nA Man\u201d\nShown at 2\n3:30- 5 and\n9:30 p. m.\nHarold Lloyd\nin a comedy\nSunday\n\u201cThe\nLeavenworth\nCase\u201d\nENTERTAINS CLERKS\nOF GILBERTS STORE\nMr. and Mrs. Julian Tischoff, Du\nbail av.. South Bend, delightfully\nentertained the sales managers and\nclerks of the M. Gilbert Son store\nMishawaka with a 6:30 o\u2019clock din\nner Thursday evening at their home.\nCovers were placed for 18 with ta\nble decorations of Jonquils. Games\nand mueic were a feature of the\nevening\u2019s entertainment. Mrs. Tisch\noff, was formerly Miss Augusta Gil\nbert, sister of Samuel and Oscar\nGilbert.\nFRED FITZSIMMONS HERE.\nFred Fitzsimmons, eon of Mr. and\nMrs. Richard Fitzsimmons, j>24 E.\nGrove et., was in Mishawaka Friday\nvisiting his parents preparatory to\nreporting at Indianapolis Saturday\nwhere he is slated to pitch an exhi\nbition baseball game against the\nBoston Red Sox. Young Fitzsim\n,mons has Just _ completed spring\ntraining with the Indianapolis club\nat its Florida training camp.\nENTERTAINS CIRCLE\nMrs. W. S. Bunn, assisted by Mrs.\nBrinner, entertained the North Side\nReading circle Thursday afternoon\nat her home, 408 W. Battell st. After\nthe business session a social hour\nwas enjoyed and refreshments\nserved.\n_\nCENTURY\nVAUDEVILLE\nBilly Farrell Co.\n\u201cTwo Generations\u201d\nOriginal songs and eccentric\ndancing. _,\nThomdyke Gazette\n\u201cTwo Bam Lawyers\u201d\npon\u2019t see this nnless you are pre\npared to hold your sides from\nmirth. _\nDuke and Duchess\n\u201cThe Dogs That Understand\u201d\nThey do everything but talk.\nPHOTOPLAYS\n\u201cRustlin. Buster\u201d\nA Universal Western.\nBaby Peggy\nin\n\u201cPeg of the Mounted\u201d\nComedy Galore.\nMATINEE TOMORROW\nIn addition to our regular pro\ngram, we will show\nRuth Roland\n\u201cRuth of the Range\u201d\nLOOK HERE!\nC. P. Gash Grocery and Market\n1402 Lincoln Way East\nSPECIALS! SPECIALS!\nSATURDAY, APRIL 12th\nPork and Beans, 3 cans...29c\nHeinz Baked Beans, 2 cans..... .25c\nSauer Kraut (Sunbeam), extra large can. 16c\nPeaches, large can..26c\nCondensed Milk, 3 large cans.. .29c\nPink Salmon, large can... 14c\nj^ll Spices, 3 cans ...i,.. 22c\nP G Soap, 10 bars...43c\nNaphtha White Soap Chips, large package.22c\nSpecials on All Fresh and Cold Meats\nBest Creamery Butter, per pound. .44c\nFresh Eggs, per dozen... .22c\nWE DELIVER AS USUAL\nTel. M-2624\nHamburger,\npound\nBeef Pot Roast,\npound\nSmoked Skinned\nHams\nHearts,\npound\nSalt Pork,\npound\n10'\n10\n20\n7\n10\nSmoked Hams, Sliced,\nLean 28C\npound\n10 pound Pail $1 OA\nPure Lard 1\u00ab'\n10\u201c\nSausage, per\npound\nLean Sugar Cured\nBacon, pound\nVeal